  <dashboards>
    <dashboard _.fcp.AccessibleZoneTabOrder.true...enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='README'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1000' minheight='800' minwidth='1000' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98000' id='3' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
            <zone forceUpdate='true' h='94375' id='5' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#e15759' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='22'>--------------------------------</run>
                <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#e15759' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='22'> ⚠️❗READ ME  ⚠️❗</run>
                <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#e15759' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='22'>--------------------------------</run>
                <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Version: 1.0</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Last Updated At: </run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10' italic='true'>2026-07-22 13:00</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Last Updated By: </run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10' italic='true'>Josh Blansett, jblansett@onterris.com</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Onterris Consulting — Analytical Air Lab Data Template Workbook</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Prepared by the Emergency Response Data Management Team</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Getting Started</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>When you open this workbook, Tableau will prompt you to enter an Onterris project number. Enter it exactly as it appears in SIERA (e.g., </run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Courier New' fontsize='10'>PROJ-123456</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>). The workbook will filter all data to that project.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>If results are not appearing as expected, verify that your project number matches the value in the </run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Courier New' fontsize='10'>projects</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'> table (the parameter is case-sensitive).</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Review Your Data Before Reporting</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>This template is not plug-and-play. Before using any outputs for client reporting or technical review, confirm the following:</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>- SIERA records are complete.</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'> Sample subtypes (e.g., Minican, Summa Canister, Integrated Air Sample) must be correctly set in SIERA. These drive which data sources apply to your project. The workbook does not use the lab&apos;s matrix field — it uses SIERA&apos;s.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>- Sample IDs match.</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'> The join between SIERA and lab results depends on </run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Courier New' fontsize='10'>primary_identifier</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'> matching </run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Courier New' fontsize='10'>samp_no</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'> exactly. Missing results are often a sample ID mismatch, not a missing lab submission.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>- Lab results have been loaded.</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'> Samples without a lab result will not appear in this workbook. Use your normal data receipt tracking to confirm all expected SDGs are in the database.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>- Review any flagged results.</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'> R-qualified results (rejected by the lab) are treated as detections in this workbook. Review them with the project TD before reporting.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>- Validation Status.</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'> The </run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Courier New' fontsize='10'>Validation Status</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'> field is populated by the DM team during internal QA/QC. Results without a validation status have not yet been reviewed.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>This Is a Template</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>This workbook standardizes data retrieval and formatting for common Onterris ER analytical matrices. It is designed to reduce repetitive build work and promote consistency, not to replace technical judgment.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Projects with non-standard sampling designs, unusual analytical methods, or custom reporting requirements will likely need workbook modifications beyond what this template provides.</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Data Source Documentation</run>
                <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Each data source tab in this workbook has a corresponding guide file in the ER Lab Tableau Sources repository on GitHub (</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Courier New' fontsize='10'>onterris/er-lab-tableau-sources</run>
                <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>). The guides document all column definitions, filter logic, unit conversions, detection rules, and known data quality caveats. Review the relevant guide before modifying a data source or troubleshooting unexpected results.</run>
              </formatted-text>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
